<div style=3D"font-size:10px;margin-top:1px">Anzeige</div><p>The short diag=
onal is the line between two vertices, which have a third vertex between th=
em. Its length equals that of the height. The long diagonal is the line bet=
ween two opposite vertices. Long diagonals and bisecting lines coincide, th=
ey intersect with the median lines and with centroid, circumcircle and inci=
rcle center in one point. To this, the regular hexagon is point symmetric a=
nd rotationally symmetric at a rotation of 60=C2=B0 or multiples of this. F=
urthermore, the regular hexagon is axially symmetric to the long diagonals =
and to the median lines.</p>
