<p>The short diagonals of the regular or equilateral hexagon form the regul=
ar <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/hexagram.php">hexagram</a>. The h=
exagon as a side surface appears in the Archimedean solids <a href=3D"https=
://rechneronline.de/pi/truncated-tetrahedron.php">truncated tetrahedron</a>=
, <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/truncated-icosahedron.php">truncat=
ed icosahedron</a>, <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/truncated-octahe=
dron.php">truncated octahedron</a>, <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/=
truncated-cuboctahedron.php">truncated cuboctahedron</a> and <a href=3D"htt=
ps://rechneronline.de/pi/truncated-icosidodecahedron.php">truncated icosido=
decahedron</a>.<br>
The hexagon is a commonly encountered shape. It is found in honeycombs, sno=
wflakes and other crystals, in organic molecules, particularly the benzene =
ring, and even in the cloud formations at Saturn's north pole. The honeycom=
b structure, which is based on honeycombs, is particularly stable with low =
material consumption and is therefore often used in technology. Hexagonal p=
arquetry is a common form of flooring and wall tiling.</p>
